p0085 = "Lord, God of my salvation, I have cried by day, and by night also before you."
p0086 = "Let my prayer come into your presence, and turn you ear to my supplication."
p0087 = "For my soul was filled with evils, and my life drew near to Hell. I was reckoned"
p0088 = "among those that go down to the Pit; I became as one that has no help,"
p0089 = "free among the dead. Like the slain that sleep in the tomb, whom you remembered"
p0090 = "no more; and they were cut off from your power. They placed me in the"
p0091 = "lowest Pit; in darkness and in the shadow of death. Your wrath lay heavy"
p0092 = "WEEKDAY MATINS 5"
p0093 = "upon me, and you brought all your waves against me. You put my friends far"
p0094 = "from me, and made me an abomination to them. I was handed over and I"
p0095 = "came out; my eyes grew weak because of my beggary. I cried to you, Lord, all"
p0096 = "the day; I stretched out my hands towards you. Will you work wonders for"
p0097 = "the dead; or will physicians raise them up again to praise you? Will any declare"
p0098 = "your mercy in the tomb, or your truth in the place of destruction? Will"
p0099 = "your wonders be known in the dark, or your righteousness in a land that has"
p0100 = "been forgotten? But to you, Lord, I have cried, and in the morning my prayer"
p0101 = "will come before you. Why have you rejected my soul, Lord; why do you turn"
p0102 = "away your face from me? I am poor and in toils since my youth; exalted, I was"
p0103 = "humbled and brought to despair. Your fierce anger overwhelmed me, and"
p0104 = "your terrors appalled me. They surrounded me like water all day long; they"
p0105 = "closed in upon me from every side. Friend and neighbour you have put far"
p0106 = "from me, and my companions because of my misery."
