p0110 = "Psalm 1022"
p0111 = "Bless the Lord, O my soul, and all that is within me, bless his holy name."
p0112 = "Bless the Lord, O my soul, and forget none of his benefits. He forgives all your"
p0113 = "iniquities; he heals all your diseases; he redeems your life from corruption"
p0114 = "and crowns you with mercy and compassion; he satisfies your desire with"
p0115 = "good things; your youth will be renewed like an eagle\u2019s. The Lord performs"
p0116 = "deeds of mercy and judgement for all who are oppressed. He made known his"
p0117 = "ways to Moses, his wishes to the children of Israel. The Lord is compassionate"
p0118 = "and merciful, long-suffering and full of mercy. He will not always be wrathful,"
p0119 = "nor will he be enraged for ever. He has not dealt with us according to our"
p0120 = "iniquities, nor rewarded us according to our sins. For, like the height of"
p0121 = "heaven above the earth, the Lord has made his mercy prevail over those that"
p0122 = "fear him. As far as the east is from the west, so far has he taken our sins from"
p0123 = "us. As a father takes pity on his children the Lord has taken pity on those who"
p0124 = "fear him. For he knows of what we are made; has remembered that we are but"
p0125 = "dust. As for man, his days are but as grass, he will blossom like a flower of the"
p0126 = "field; for when a wind has passed over it, it will be no more and will know its"
p0127 = "place no longer. But the mercy of the Lord is for ever and ever upon those"
p0128 = "who fear him; and his justice upon their children\u2019s children, upon those who"
p0129 = "keep his covenant and remember his commandments to do them. The Lord"
p0130 = "has prepared his throne in heaven and his kingdom rules over all. Bless the"
p0131 = "Lord, all you his Angels, powerful in strength, who perform his word, and"
p0132 = "listen to the voice of his words. Bless the Lord, all you his Powers, his Ministers"
p0133 = "who do his will. Bless the Lord, all you his works. In every place of his"
p0134 = "dominion, bless the Lord, O my soul!"
