p0142 = "your sight no one living can be justified. For the enemy pursued my soul;"
p0143 = "humbled my life to the ground; made me dwell in darkness, like those for"
p0144 = "ever dead. My spirit in me grew weary, and my heart was troubled within"
p0145 = "me. I remembered days of old; I meditated on all your works. I made the"
p0146 = "works of your hands my meditation. I stretched out my hands towards you;"
p0147 = "my soul thirsted for you like a waterless land. Hear me swiftly, O Lord; my"
p0148 = "spirit has failed. Do not turn your face from me, or I shall be like those who go"
p0149 = "down to the Pit. Make me hear of your mercy in the morning, for I have"
p0150 = "hoped in you. Make known to me the way in which I should walk, for to you I"
p0151 = "have lifted up my soul. Deliver me from my enemies, Lord; I have run to you"
p0152 = "for shelter. Teach me to do your will, for you are my God. Your good Spirit"
p0153 = "will guide me in an upright land. For your name\u2019s sake, O Lord, you will give"
p0154 = "me life. In your justice you will bring my soul out of trouble; in your mercy"
p0155 = "slay my enemies, and destroy all those who afflict my soul, for I am your servant."
