p0300 = "Lord, have mercy. Lord, have mercy. Lord, have mercy. Glory to the"
p0301 = "father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit."
p0302 = duplicates_en_uk_lash.d0698
p0303 = "Have mercy on me, O God, in accordance with your great mercy. According"
p0304 = "to the multitude of your compassion blot out my offence. Wash me thoroughly"
p0305 = "from my wickedness, and cleanse me from my sin. For I acknowledge"
p0306 = "my wickedness, and my sin is ever before me. Against you alone I have"
p0307 = "sinned and done what is evil in your sight, that you may be justified in your"
p0308 = "words and win when you are judged. For see, in wickedness I was conceived"
p0309 = "and in sin my mother bore me. For see, you have loved truth; you have shown"
p0310 = "me the hidden and secret things of your wisdom. You will sprinkle me with"
p0311 = "hyssop and I shall be cleansed. You will wash me and I shall be made whiter"
p0312 = "than snow. You will make me hear of joy and gladness; the bones which have"
p0313 = "been humbled will rejoice. Turn away your face from my sins and blot out all"
p0314 = "my iniquities. Create a clean heart in me, O God, and renew a right Spirit"
p0315 = "within me. Do not cast me out from your presence, and do not take your Holy"
p0316 = "Spirit from me. Give me back the joy of your salvation, and establish me with"
p0317 = "your sovereign Spirit. I will teach transgressors your ways, and sinners will"
p0318 = "turn to you again. O God, the God of my salvation, deliver me from bloodshed"
p0319 = "and my tongue will rejoice at your justice. Lord, you will open my lips,"
p0320 = "and my mouth will proclaim your praise. For if you had wanted a sacrifice, I"
p0321 = "would have given it. You will not take pleasure in burnt offerings. A sacrifice"
p0322 = "to God is a broken spirit; a broken and a humbled heart God will not despise."
p0323 = "Do good to Sion, Lord, in your good pleasure; and let the walls of Jerusalem"
p0324 = "be rebuilt. Then you will be well pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, oblation"
p0325 = "and whole burnt offerings. Then they will offer calves upon your altar."
