p1038 = "NOTE ON THE APOSTLE AND GOSPEL"
p1039 = "If the Liturgy is not celebrated, it is customary to read the Apostle and Gospel"
p1040 = "of the day at the end of the First Hour, after the prayer, \u2018Christ the true light\u2019."
p1041 = "The Litany of Fervent Intercession, \u2018Let us all say\u2019, is omitted at Matins and"
p1042 = "said after the Gospel. The Dismissal follows the Litany."
p1043 = "[If the First Hour is not said, the Apostle and Gospel may be read immediately"
p1044 = "after the Apolytikion and its Theotokion at the end of Matins, before the"
p1045 = "final Litany and Dismissal.]"
p1046 = "NOTE ON THE SINGING OF THE CANONS"
p1047 = "The Canons are dealt with in a number of different ways in different churches"
p1048 = "and monasteries. On the Holy Mountain the most complete method is as follows."
p1049 = "The odd numbered Odes are begun by the first choir and the even by the"
p1050 = "second."
p1051 = "WEEKDAY MATINS 27"
p1052 = "On ordinary days, including Sundays, the first choir sings the Irmos from"
p1053 = "the 1st Canon in the Paraklitiki, the second sings an appropriate verse [normally"
p1054 = "\u2018Glory to you, our God, glory to you\u2019] and then the first Troparion of"
p1055 = "the Canon."
p1056 = "The first choir then sings the first verse from the Biblical Canticle and the"
p1057 = "second troparion. The rest of the Ode is sung in the same way."
p1058 = "The Ode from the first Canon in the Paraklitiki normally consists of an Irmos"
p1059 = "and 5 Troparia, the second of 4 Troparia and that from the Menaion of 4."
p1060 = "The total should therefore always come to 14. There are 12 verses from the"
p1061 = "Biblical canticle, hence the need for a simple refrain before the first troparion."
p1062 = "The Irmos is always sung without any preliminary verse or refrain. Only the"
p1063 = "Irmos of the first Canon is sung."
p1064 = "If the Typikon directs that the Irmi are to be doubled, which occurs on"
p1065 = "more important feasts, then the Irmos is sung twice, once by each choir, with"
p1066 = "no \u2018refrain\u2019."
p1067 = "If the Saint of the day is \u2018feasted\u2019, that is has at least one Doxastikon at"
p1068 = "Vespers, then his, her or their Canon is sung to six, not four, two troparia being"
p1069 = "sung twice, and two troparia from the Canons in the Paraklitiki are"
p1070 = "dropped, normally those to the Martyrs in the first Canon. If two Canons from"
p1071 = "the Menaion are prescribed, then the second Canon from the Paraklitiki is"
p1072 = "omitted."
p1073 = "On the feasts when the Paraklitiki is not used, the first canon is normally"
p1074 = "the Little Canon of Supplication to the Mother of God. Some feasts have their"
p1075 = "own Canon to the Mother of God."
p1076 = "On Saturdays the first canon in the Paraklitiki, to the Prophets and Martyrs,"
p1077 = "is traditionally replaced by that of the patron of the church or monastery."
p1078 = "These rules cannot be complete, since many canons have more troparia"
p1079 = "than usual in some odes, or on occasion fewer. This means that sometimes a"
p1080 = "troparion has either to be omitted or doubled. It is the duty of the Canonarch"
p1081 = "to ensure that mistakes are not made and that the count is always fourteen."
p1082 = "At the end of the 3rd, 6th, 8th and 9th Odes, the Irmos of the last Canon,"
p1083 = "normally that from the Menaion, is sung as Katavasia."
